    <body>
      <section eId="sec_453_A">
        <num>453-A</num>
        <heading>Payments for non-recurring adoption expenses</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_453_A__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the state has determined cannot or shall not be returned to the\nhome of his or her parents; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_453_A__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the state has first determined:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_453_A__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>is a handicapped child as defined in subdivision two of section\nfour hundred fifty-one of this title, or is a hard-to-place child as\ndefined in paragraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_453_A__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of subdivision three of section four hundred\nfifty-one of this title; and\n  (ii) a reasonable, but unsuccessful effort has been made to place the\nchild with appropriate adoptive parents without adoption assistance.\nSuch an effort need not be made where such efforts would not be in the\nbest interests of the child because of such factors as the existence of\nsignificant emotional ties with prospective adoptive parents while in\nthe care of such parents as a foster child.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
